AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1307 House Bill No. 127*
by adding the following new sections immediately preceding the effective date section and
renumbering that section accordingly:
SECTION __. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 67-4-3202(a), is amended by
deleting subdivision (4) in its entirety.
SECTION __. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 67-4-3202(g)(2)(C), is amended by
deleting the subdivision and substituting instead the following:
(C) No local government may levy a surcharge on a business tax under
subdivision (a)(2) or a surcharge on a residential development tax under subdivision
(a)(6) that separately exceeds the rate of twenty percent (20%) of the current applicable
rate of the business tax or residential development tax.
AND FURTHER AMEND by adding the following language as a new subdivision (3) in the
amendatory language of Section 3 and renumbering the existing subdivisions accordingly:
(3) "Public transit system" means any mass transit system intended for shared
passenger transport services to the general public, together with any building, structure,
appurtenance, utility, transport support facility, transport vehicles, service vehicles,
parking facility, or any other facility, structure, vehicle, or property needed to operate the
transportation facility or provide connectivity for the transportation facility to any other
non-mass transit system transportation infrastructure, including, but not limited to,
interstates, highways, roads, streets, alleys, and sidewalks;
